Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with the implementation of a calculus, which is a core topic in programming languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the meta-theory of a new notion called "useful sharing", which is related to the study of logic in computer science. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents an abstract machine and an optimization that improve the efficiency of the implementation, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science): The paper discusses the complexity of implementing a calculus and introduces a new notion, which are topics related to theoretical computer science. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents an implementation of a calculus and discusses its practical aspects, which are topics related to software engineering.
